---
import Layout from '../../components/Layout.astro';
import MetaHarnessChamber from '../../components/v22/MetaHarnessChamber.astro';
import { repositoryCommits } from '../../data/observatory';
---
<Layout title="Meta Harness — Systems Observatory" description="Evidence-gated execution harness for coding-agent workflows: phases, packets, validation, proof, checkpoints, and continuation." canonicalPath="/systems/meta-harness/">
  <section class="flagship-hero harness-flagship"><div class="shell"><span>OPEN-SOURCE FLAGSHIP / HARNESS</span><h1>Make long-horizon agent work bounded, inspectable, and resumable.</h1><p>Meta Harness turns a large implementation specification into dependency-ordered phases and slices, bounded worker packets, validation gates, proof ledgers, checkpoints, and an explicit next action.</p><div><a class="signal-button" href="https://github.com/smgpulse007/meta-harness">Repository ↗</a><small>PINNED SOURCE / {repositoryCommits.metaHarness.slice(0,12)}</small></div></div></section>
  <section class="v22-scene"><div class="shell scene-heading"><div><span>01 / EXECUTION CHAMBER</span><h2>The protocol is the product.</h2></div><p>This walkthrough is derived from actual schemas and checked-in examples. It is not a live agent or fabricated success demonstration.</p></div><div class="shell"><MetaHarnessChamber/></div></section>
  <section class="v22-scene harness-contracts"><div class="shell scene-heading"><div><span>02 / CONTRACT SURFACES</span><h2>Every handoff carries state and proof.</h2></div><p>The same contracts support CLI, MCP, adapter, skill, and instruction-emitter surfaces.</p></div><div class="shell contract-orbit">{['PhaseManifest','SlicePlan','SlicePacket','ProofLedger','Checkpoint','NextAction'].map((name,i)=><article><span>{String(i+1).padStart(2,'0')}</span><strong>{name}</strong><p>{['Acceptance, validation, dependencies','Scope, owner, evidence requirements','Changed files, outputs, risks','Claims linked to evidence paths','Durable state and carry-forward risk','Continue, review, stop, or block'][i]}</p></article>)}</div></section>
  <section class="v22-scene limitation-field"><div class="shell"><div><span>BOUNDARY CONDITIONS</span><h2>Pre-1.0. Source-installed. Read-only first.</h2></div><ul><li>Adapter support varies.</li><li>Fake-adapter simulation is not command-verified release proof.</li><li>The harness does not guarantee correctness or autonomy.</li><li>External side effects require explicit approval.</li></ul><p>Independent of the 2026 paper with a similar “Meta-Harness” title unless repository history establishes otherwise.</p></div></section>
</Layout>
